<plot>Havana-Gila is a short film about six Cubans and a Jew. The story is about a Cuban girl "Caridad" and a Jewish New Yorker "Scotty" who fall in love. Caridad brings Scotty home to meet her very Cuban, Catholic and Conservative family. Watch as Scotty tries to break the news that he is Jewish to her traditional Catholic family and Caridad tries to stop him every step of the way.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?231825</url></doc>
